      • setPropertiesInitialized

        public void setPropertiesInitialized(boolean initialized)
        Indicates all the other managed properties have been set. JSF 1.1 does not provide a way of knowing that out-of-the-box, therefore this is a workaround which defines a managed property named propertiesInitialized that, when set triggers this method. As JSF 1.1 guarantees managed properties are set in the order defined in the configuration file, defining this as the last property effectively means this method will be called when all other properties have been set.
        Parameters:
        initialized - a boolean which should always be true, since calling this method indeed means all other properties have been initialized
